<userid>107858836993009220070< /userid><username>David Rodriguez</username><date>1609361236765<//date><rating>5</rating><Review>This is a good moderate hike. On a clear day, the views from the top are amazing - you can see Downtown LA and Catalina Island. There isn't much shade on the trail so on warmer days you'll want to bring plenty of water and sunscreen. Also, parking on most Whittier city streets is by permit only, so make sure you adhere to posted parking signs. I've had to park as far as one mile away from the trailhead to avoid getting a parking ticket.< /Review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNSHtbXde2IhSmLDeMrde_Y32CwyFApjrbh-l8C=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN6i-csKP-3WNn2stbRblZoW6Fb2hLEtW2MQsS_=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPngpDvswl0VAKOmqrTfvWX_g_fHmp0VPrfLLqW=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pictures>< Response>

< review>
Nice spot to take a quick hike. I used is a lot to get my 1.5 year old son used to hiking in a backpack. On it's own it's not a very strenuous hike. Add a toddler to your back and a wife that wants to prove she's faster than you and you can get your heart pumping. There are tons of smaller trails that you can venture off to. Some lead back to where you started, some are dead ends, and some will take you far from where you need to be so pay attention.<//review>

<user>110792431341706254499</user>< user_name>
India M. Clamp</user_name>
< Date>
1544676184222< /Date>
<Rate>3< /Rate>< text>
Many meandering hikes in this area, yet on this day (after the rain) a view opened up rather unexpectedly and it was not at all torturous hiking with Danny---UCLA---and Addy on this route.

Historically overflowing with tales from Turnbull Canyon (named for a Scotsman) and the "Electrodome" which "for the wise" not too difficult to spot and locate.

Time in all things. Vistas from Los Angeles to Ranchos Palos Verdes were witnessed and the hike---though damp---was a delight. Full moon greeted en-route to the Spanish Revival Palace by C.M. Hutchinson.<//text>

< UserId.>
103088809791562103332</UserId.>
<user_name>Kirk< /user_name><Time>1536815777255<//Time>< Rating>
3</Rating>
< review>
Google recommend that I try out Teriyaki Sun as a new restaurant near me, and I decided to try it tonight.   It wasn't very difficult to get here and parking wasn't bad at 6pm.  The dining area is fairly plain and simple, but very clean. The decor is Island inspired, with an island / Asian fusion menu. I ordered the chicken teriyaki, with fried rice and a coke. It came with a salad that is tasty, and crisp, with a creamy ginger dressing.  The potato salad was not what I was expecting, but I am very happy with what was served.  The potatoes seem to be hand mashed with circular sliced carrots and macaroni.  It was very mildly seasoned, which brought out more potato taste, which I think is a bit unique for an island inspired side, kudos for that.  The chicken has a mild marinade if any at all, but is grilled perfectly.  It is boneless thigh meat.  It is served with a side of teriyaki sauce that is tasty.  The fried rice is good with egg, corn, carrots, onion, and green pepper.  All in all, the food is not over seasoned, which is a huge plus for me.  The portions are more than adequate for all but the heaviest of eaters.  Google referred me to Teriyaki Sun, and I am glad they did.  I wish it was closer to my home so I could go more often.  I certainly suggest giving it a try for when looking for good food but nothing fancy.   As always, I rate stars as follows: 1- not good all around, 2- some good good value, but pretty common and nothing stood out, 3- a solid choice all around, 4- one of my favorites, 5- a great experience all around and very unique for the area.< /review>

<UserId.>109891920205890072466<//UserId.><user_name>Carlos Vallejo< /user_name>< Date>
1550280648970< /Date>
<Rating>4<//Rating>< Text>
Decent ramen place.  Got the miso ramen on a couple of occasions and was happy with it.  The place is really large but every time there were only a few other customers there.  My friend got the seafood ramen and was happy with it.  Vegetable tempura was overbreaded and undercooked.  Wouldn't get it again.

Lunch special I got on a separate day was very underwhelming.  I'm used to bento lunch boxes coming with a great deal more than just the chicken, rice, and 4 Cali rolls.  Especially considering you can go to Sushi & Galbi less than a couple miles away and get twice the stuff (+soup, tempura, and salad) at a lower cost.  Definitely would not get their  lunch special again but would still hit them up for ramen.

Service has always been friendly here.  Zero complaints.  You pay up front before you eat so it's a little weird because if you pay with a card you tip BEFORE the service but even so I've never had cause for raising a concern.

Food comes out hot and the place is clean.  Just watch out for that front door because it is a couple pulls away from falling off its hinges.< /Text>

We have to pay so much for medical care and it's extremely unfortunate when you don't feel like the doctors are treating your issues with any urgency. It only takes a few minutes to call and let me know what the results are.

Some cons with this clinic:
- They have nurses but all physician assistants are offsite so you have a video cal with them. It's super awkward because the video sometimes cuts out and the PA isn't able to assess you in person
- it only took ~10 minutes to get me connected to a PA but I've read that it sometimes takes close to an hour
- They have close to no equipment here so you have to do any screening at another site

<Rating>5</Rating>< review>
Truly an amazing experience! I woke up with the beginnings of UTI symptoms on July 4th. I immediately started guzzling water. By noon I needed extra strength Tylenol and a heating pad for my leftside back pain. You women know what I am talking about! I called action urgent Care and their answering service made me a 10am appointment for the next day. When I arrived at Action urgent Care inside the Safeway on Folsom Blvd Kat, a nurse, greeted us and started with our virtual visit. She took all info privately and paperless (iPad). After a urine sample dip test and listening to my heart and lungs with a special BLUETOOTH stethescope and entering more info into the secure web based software she turned on the big screen and after a moment the doctor came into an exam room and sat down. This virtual visit went the same as an in person visit but was quick as he had reviewed Kats findings. He asked me few questions and made a decision about antibiotics and a pain med. Kat made me a follow-up visit to go over culture results and we were done. Kat was friendly, efficient, patient centered and very competent. I Love Virtual Care!!! Thanks Action Urgent Care!< /review>

<text>This is a place that specializes in boba! I go here or get it Door Dashed whenever I can. They have a pretty large selection and readily offer milk substitutes. They carry milk teas, smoothies, lattes, teas, taiyaki (depending if the machine is warmed up or not, an order of this may take up to 10 minutes to make), slushies, waffles, and a selection of Marrianne's ice cream. They also have a few Korean style snacks. My favorites include taro milk tea with boba (boba is 50 cents extra), Earl Grey milk tea and rose garden milk tea. They also offer several toppings like flavored popping boba, mochi, clear boba, and a couple others. Customer service has always been excellent and quick.< /text><user_id>111492624946899057591<//user_id><Pics>None<//Pics><date>1616108745837</date><user_name>Abi Kirikawa< /user_name><rate>5</rate>< Resp>

Drinks are fresh and sweet - but not too sweet. The secret is in the tea, I think. It's brewed just right and doesn't taste like the bagged stuff you can get from the supermarket.

< Name>
Jessicah Jin<//Name>
< Time>
1594499934064< /Time>
< Rating>
5</Rating>
< Text>
Delicious desserts!
Drinks are fresh and sweet - but not too sweet. The secret is in the tea, I think. It's brewed just right and doesn't taste like the bagged stuff you can get from the supermarket.
As for the tapioca boba, it's just the right level of chewy and savory. And the egg waffles are crispy on the outside, while still fluffy on the inside.
I love stopping by whenever I have a craving for something sweet or refreshing.
My favorites: oolong black tea with boba when I want something cooling but not too sweet OR passion fruit green tea when I want something sweet and tart (they don't use syrup, they use passion fruit preserves so it tastes actual like passion fruit).</Text>

< review>
I really wanted to give this place a go. I searched it on Yelp to see if it was AYCE, which one reviewer simply confirmed "yes." I Arrived no later than 2:10, and was seated at the sushi bar. I proceeded to confirm with the hostess if they had AYCE, and she stoically responded that it ends at 2. I humbly stated to her that I wasn't informed that there was a time limit, and respectfully asked her if I could be accommodated for it. She rushfully went to her register and told me that she couldn't. Now; what peeves me is that there was exactly one party of two in the entire restaurant. Maybe I'm old fashioned, but if I was hurting for business on a hot Summer day, I would give my customer the befinit of the doubt and accommodate them. Most sushi bars serve their lunch special from at least 2:30 to 3:30. Again, I was less than a sixth of an hour's tardy to their infeisable AYCE special, and was given no leeway to give them my at least $40 business; when there was next to ZERO business to begin with. If you take anything from this review, make it the last sentence I just elaborated. Sushi is too expensive to be snooty about. This place obviously needs to go.

Just read more reviews before posting this to Yelp, then Google. No surprise to see "Terrible customer service" in every fourth review. Guess there's a silver lining in that one :)

Hit up Mr. Sushi on Valencia & Cinema if you're jonesing for quality AYCE sushi all day. Too bad This place wasted my lunch time, probably I'd have just gone there as usual.<//review>

<Text>I love this little office chair!

First, it‚Äôs adorable.  It‚Äôs a really stylish design, and the color is very pretty.  I love the velvet material.  Second, it‚Äôs just the right size for my small office and desk.

The chair came quickly, was very easy to put together, and works well.  I love the forward tilt - it helps me maintain a proper posture while sitting at my desk for hours.

< Review>
We bought my sister a fire place insert model EP24789 fireplace at Christmas.  This insert is a fire hazard.  We tested it for a few minutes to make sure it worked. It came with a 15 amp plug. During a cold snap she put it on the high setting for 15 minutes to get the chill out of the room. As she went to unplug it, the plug was hot. She had an electrician look at the outlet, which was fine and that the fireplace and/or plug must be defected.  After contacting Costway, we were told she needed a 20 amp outlet.  We wrote them back asking why does the fireplace have a 15 amp plug, and the booklet and website state 15 amp?  They said they would take it back and refund us only if we had the original box and wrapping.  This was a Christmas gift, it had been over 2 months, we did not save the box or original wrapping. <UserId.>118354030823516137269</UserId.><name>Amy Gockley<//name><time>1616603332987</time><Rating>5< /Rating><text>I recently received this kitchen island from Costway, and it is perfect for my small kitchen. I really needed something that would provide me with not only a nice prep and beverage space, but also some extra storage. This kitchen island boasts two cabinets, one larger and one smaller, as well as two drawers. The shelves in the cabinets are easily adjustable to fit your needs. The cabinets open easy, but are also secure with a magnet closure. The drawers glide open like a dream, but have a stopper, as to not accidentally pull the entire drawer out. If you have kids, like I do, you know how important it is for those drawer stoppers to work. The island also features a knife block on the end. One of my favorite features of this island is that it has wheels to easily move it. This is so convenient for cleaning underneath and behind it. The handle, that is on the end, also helps you easily move the island, but also can be used as a kitchen towel or paper towel rack. Overall, this kitchen island is aesthetically pleasing. The materials used to make this are pretty sturdy. One thing I‚Äôd like to touch on is the directions and packaging. I can‚Äôt tell you how many times I‚Äôve bought things elsewhere where the directions are terrible, and all the hardware is thrown into one bag. That is not the case at all with this! The directions were very clear and easy to follow, and all hardware was bagged separately and labeled. This made putting the island together so much quicker. If you are on the fence about an item, don‚Äôt hesitate! You won‚Äôt be able to find the same quality for the price. Plus, don‚Äôt forget you get fast and free shipping. Do yourself a favor and order; you won‚Äôt be sorry!

I was also in the market for a bunk bed for my kids room. I needed one with solid construction, so it would grow with them but also wanted one that was not going to break the bank. This bunk bed definitely fit the bill. After ordering, it took about 2-3 days to arrive. Everything was well packed and protected. It took my husband about an hour to assemble. The process of putting it together goes so much faster, as they have everything clearly labeled and hardware is sorted out into individual bags. One thing my husband really liked was that the mattress slats were tethered together for each bunk. This takes the guess work out of how many to use or how far to space them. The wood is pretty solid and not the really cheap stuff. The bed is very stable, and I like that it is not squeaky if my kids move, like some other beds. The bottom bunk sits higher off the ground and provides ample room to store stuff under the bed, if you would like. Another plus is that this bed is versatile and can be separated into 2 twin size beds, if we choose to do so. Overall, my kids are absolutely thrilled with their bunk bed, and so am I.</text>< pics>

<review>I have been very impressed with COSTWAY's products and service. I have purchased several products, all good quality, great packaging and excellent customer service. I have purchased a compact folding treadmill (LOVE IT) Adjustable folding ladder (perfect for my cabin) Mini Circular saw (wish I had this the last 6 months). I am very happy with all my purchases.

Absolutely loving my Costway Modern Tufted Accent Chair:  Mid Century Modern Upholstered Accent Chair, w/ Rubber Wood Legs, Button Tufted Armchair, Linen Fabric Single Sofa for Living Room, Bedroom, Office (costway.com)
My wife really enjoys curling up in this chair with a good book. The material is comfortable yet durable enough for our dog Piper to get in a nap on the chair (until she is caught üòä and we say get down) I personally like the mix of comfort design this chair offers, the bottom cushion is firm yet comfortable for long sitting times while the back support has a soft pillow design which I find very relaxing.
I really like that the back support can be easily removed with a firm pull, this lightens the load and makes it easier to move the chair from room to room and through tight spaces. The construction of this chair is very solid. I found it extremely easy to put together. The most amount of time assembling this chair is fastening the legs to the base. Each leg on the chair has 4 bolts that insure a secure fix to the chair base. Like any product take your time and read the assembly instructions.
Absolutely loving this Costway Modern Tufted Accent Chair! So pleased with the purchase!<//review>< Pictures>

Love My New Exercise Machine!

I was so looking forward to receive my Vibration Plate Exercise Machine with Loop Bands Home from Costway. Delivery was really quick and it is very easy to assemble. Simply just unpack, plug and go.

What I like about this machine is it works out on different parts of your body depending on how you position yourself. < Text>
Received a fire pit from them, really was looking forward to this particular one as the thatched metal pattern matches our rattan furniture. We received it and it needed to be put together which wasn't too strenuous or difficult as my daughter helped me (see pic). I did notice that the piece the gas tank sits on looks different than the symmetrical piece shown in the instructions, but the gas tank still fit fine (see pic). Anyway, looks great, throws off a great adjustable flame, comes with a top to cover flame area if you'd like to use it as a table. You need to be careful not to pile the rocks too high or that cover won't fit, just takes a little give and take here and there with the lava rock arrangement, Anyway, again, Costway has provided a more premium looking product, IMO, for a lower price. Really happy with it. Recommended.</Text>

<Name>Tim Hobbs< /Name><text>The chair comes disassembled and took about 30-45 minutes to put together at a leisurely pace. The instructions could be a bit easier to understand but if you have assembled any furniture it is pretty much the same thing. The hardware comes in a nice little package so you don't have to dig through the box to find parts.

I was impressed by the overall quality. The feel is nice. My daughter thought it was really cool :)

The chair is comfortable and the adjustment options are nice: up/down, arms up/down and swivel in/out, and the recline feature is cool though not sure how practical. To be honest when I tested it out it went so far back I thought I was going to fall backwards. I don't even think I reclined it all the way! The one thing that would be nice is if the arm width could be adjusted - right now it would require adjusting the screws.

I work full time from home so I am pretty decently versed in chair prices and for any decent chair you would pay the same or more, so it seems like a decent price and value. I know that many similar "gamer" chairs can run up to 5x more.<//text><Rate>4< /Rate></record>

We opened the box, there was no damage to it, everything was in tact and packed perfectly, and then we plugged it in, connected the water supply and turned it on.
As soon as we turned it on the tub started to fill with water. It was able to make ice but the ice fell in the tub of water. I called Costway and was instructed to email their customer service. I couldn't speak to anyone all concerns were to be emailed. I did that and their response times is 24-48hrs. After several emails back and forth sending videos and pics they said the machine was missing the plug and they would send me one. They sent me the plug for the unit 3 different times because i never received it. I finally received it in July, installed the plug, turned the machine on and no leaks! Woo hoo, now I can finally use my ice maker! NOT!!!! Although the machine didn't leak it produced very soft ice and couldn't keep it frozen. All the ice that was made would fall in the tub and melt, until the tub was finally filled with water and half melted ice. I've been trying to call Costway for the past week. No ring, just busy signal. <user_name>Stefan Gombas< /user_name>< Date>
1600121129390<//Date>
<rate>2</rate><text>I purchased an office/gaming desk off of Amazon. First thing to note is that this product is claimed to be made by Tangkula, which is actually a company based out of California by the name of Costway. The desk arrived in two separate packages when it could easily been one, which leads me to believe the desktop and support system come from different locations...little odd but whatever.

Both boxes arrive and I start assembly. There are a few surface imperfections in faux wood grain as shown in picture. ‚ÄúWooden‚Äù pieces and the black mid section are adjoined by small wooden pegs and reinforced by metal runners. Seems like the hole thing should more securely fastened together. Hexagonal bolts fasten everything together, but poor quality control made it rough to assemble as receiving holes were not properly reamed out.

Next my issue dealing with customer support arises. I found that my packages did not include 2 of the parts necessary to complete construction. I contacted the actual company Costway through their email found on their website and through here on Amazon. Only way to contact them is through email, and it took a long time to finally get a hold of someone. We spoke via email over the course of several days because they only answer in the middle of the night (EASTERN US TIMEZONE). First they told me they didn‚Äôt have those parts in stock and it would be 25-30 days until they got more in from China. They offered to compensate me $30 for my wait, but I said no and that if the parts were not there within a week I‚Äôd like a refund. So ‚Äúsurprise‚Äù they decided to send me an entire half of the order with all the hardware and legs (could of just taken those missing parts out of the box). Customer service was not rude, but hard to reach and odd to deal with.

After I got my replacement parts I finish putting the desk together as detailed. The remaining bolts holes could also used reamed as I said before. Washers would also help prevent any over torque since they need to be securely tightened to prevent any wobbling. As shown in the picture there is a small 1/8‚Äù gap on one side between faux wood and black mid section due to poor quality control.

Overall the desk looks nice minus the surface imperfections and panel gaps. The adjustable legs are nice since I live in an older home with uneven floors. That does not excuse the missing parts, hard to reach customer service, and poor quality control. I would not make another purchase from Tangkula AKA Costway AKA Any Other Brand They Use.

PROS:
Simple steps for constructions
Looks nice
Adjustable feet

CONS:
Poor quality control
Missing parts upon arrival
Hard to reach manufacturer
Design flaws (should have washers)<//text>< pictures>

I couldn't speak to anyone all concerns were to be emailed. I did that and their response times is 24-48hrs. After several emails back and forth sending videos and pics they said the machine was missing the plug and they would send me one. They sent me the plug for the unit 3 different times because i never received it. I finally received it in July, installed the plug, turned the machine on and no leaks! All the ice that was made would fall in the tub and melt, until the tub was finally filled with water and half melted ice. < Text>
I purchased a GO PLUS Magnetic Exercise Bike Stationary Belt Drive Indoor Cycling Bike. Upon receiving I noticed there was an incomplete part discovered during assembly. I contacted Costway via email and twitter with picture and information. They responded and sent me the complete molded part. It took some time to recieve the part as that was explained in the initial correspondence and it was close to the time Costway customer service said it would take. While I waited for part I was able to make bike functional in the meantime. But needless to say the bike is solid now with the complete molded part. I give the review 4 stars for that reason. It's winter/snow where I live right now and I have no concern about the elements outside because I have a workout room set up and now this indoor bike to complete my 24 hour fitness area in my place. I'm 56 and I bike often in the summer outside. It's an important part of my complete workouts and have spent more than a few winters suffering by not having that option indoors. I do not have that concern anymore. Anytime day or night it can be GO TIME on this bike. The heavy 30 lb flywheel is just right. The belt drive is whisper quiet. And the magnets. Oh man.... I just rotated the adjustable knob in a full 360¬∞to move the magnets closer to the flywheel. The new resistance level is kickin my butt so my numbers for speed and distance are lower of course on the LCD monitor that also observes time, calorie and heart rate. But that's what great workouts are about. Time to climb that mountain all over again. I can't begin to describe how great the workouts are with this spinner bike. It's full-on intense and worth every minute. Just what I was hoping for when I bought it. I wish the LCD monitor would show miles instead of kilometers but it's not difficult to calculate your kilometers to miles, kph to mph, etc. That would be the other reason I gave 4 stars for this review. In closing. Thanks Costway for a great spinner/indoor bike. I bought this on Cyber Monday and Costway provided a hard to turn down discount that also  included free shipping that swayed me from buying another bike from a different company. This Go Plus bike may not be a famous brand name. But at this point it is my experience and opinion that I would put it right up there with any spinner bike that has comparable specs/features.</Text>
